api_list.name: getDelegateeDetails
api_list.description: Retrieve the details of an organization with which you are connected.

api_list.name: createAdministrator
api_list.description: Creates a new administrator in your organization. An email will be sent for this administrator to confirm and configure their account.

optional_parameters.name: isReadOnly
optional_parameters.description: Whether this administrator can perform write operations.

optional_parameters.name: phone
optional_parameters.description: The administrator's phone number.

api_list.name: createDestination
api_list.description: Destinations represent the location details for tasks, including exact coordinate and address information.

required_parameters.name: addressNumber
required_parameters.description: The number component of this address, it may also contain letters.

optional_parameters.name: addressApartment
optional_parameters.description: The suite or apartment number, or any additional relevant information.

optional_parameters.name: addressState
optional_parameters.description: The name of the state, province or jurisdiction.

optional_parameters.name: addressName
optional_parameters.description: A name associated with this address.

optional_parameters.name: coordinates
optional_parameters.description: The longitude, latitude coma-separated. If missing, the API will geocode based on the address details provided. Note that geocoding may slightly modify the format of the address properties.

optional_parameters.name: addressPostalCode
optional_parameters.description: The postal or zip code.

api_list.name: createDestinationFromRaw
api_list.description: Destinations represent the location details for tasks, including exact coordinate and address information.

required_parameters.name: unparsed
required_parameters.description: A complete address specified in a single, unparsed string where the various elements are separated by commas.

api_list.name: createRecipient
api_list.description: A recipient is an organization’s customer and a target for a task, that is, whom the task is being delivered to.

required_parameters.name: phone
required_parameters.description: A unique, valid phone number as per the recipient’s organization’s country.

optional_parameters.name: skipPhoneNumberValidation
optional_parameters.description: Whether to skip validation of this recipient's phone number. An E.164-like number is still required (must start with +), however the API will not enforce any country-specific validation rules.

optional_parameters.name: notes
optional_parameters.description: Notes for this recipient: these are global notes that should not be task- or destination-specific.

optional_parameters.name: skipSMSNotifications
optional_parameters.description: Whether this recipient has requested to not receive SMS notifications. Defaults to false if not provided.

api_list.name: createTask
api_list.description: Create new task

required_parameters.name: destinationId
required_parameters.description: The ID of the task's destination

required_parameters.name: recipientsIds
required_parameters.description: An array containing zero or one IDs of the task's recipients

optional_parameters.name: notes
optional_parameters.description: Notes for the task.

optional_parameters.name: serviceTime
optional_parameters.description: The number of minutes to be spent by the worker on arrival at this task's destination, for route optimization purposes.

optional_parameters.name: merchant
optional_parameters.description: The ID of the organization that will be displayed to the recipient of the task. Defaults to the creating organization. If you perform deliveries on behalf of a connected organization and want to display their name, logo, and branded notifications, provide their organization ID.

optional_parameters.name: executor
optional_parameters.description: The ID of the organization that will be responsible for fulfilling the task. Defaults to the creating organization. If you delegate your deliveries to a third party, provide their organization ID.

optional_parameters.name: completeBefore
optional_parameters.description: A date Y-m-d H:m:s for the latest time the task should be completed.

optional_parameters.name: completeAfter
optional_parameters.description: A date Y-m-d H:m:s for the earliest time the task should be completed.

optional_parameters.name: pickupTask
optional_parameters.description: Whether the task is a pickup task.

optional_parameters.name: container
optional_parameters.description: The container to which to append this task. Defaults to the creator organization container.

optional_parameters.name: autoAssign
optional_parameters.description: The automatic assignment options for the newly created task. You may not provide a container if using automatic assignment.

optional_parameters.name: quantity
optional_parameters.description: The number of units to be dropped off while completing this task, for route optimization purposes.

optional_parameters.name: dependencies
optional_parameters.description: One or more IDs of tasks which must be completed prior to this task.

api_list.name: createTeam
api_list.description: Teams are named entities that bring together administrators and workers belonging to the same organization. Teams have hubs from where its workers may start and end their shifts.

required_parameters.name: name
required_parameters.description: A unique name for the team.

optional_parameters.name: hub
optional_parameters.description: The ID of the team's hub.

optional_parameters.name: workers
optional_parameters.description: An array of worker IDs.

optional_parameters.name: managers
optional_parameters.description: An array of managing administrator IDs.

api_list.name: createWebhook
api_list.description: Webhooks make it possible for your application to be notified of important system events, as soon as these take place within Onfleet.

required_parameters.name: trigger
required_parameters.description: The number corresponding to the trigger condition on which the webhook should fire: http://docs.onfleet.com/docs/webhooks

required_parameters.name: url
required_parameters.description: The URL that Onfleet should issue a request against as soon as the trigger condition is met.

optional_parameters.name: threshold
optional_parameters.description: For trigger 1, the time threshold in seconds; for trigger 2, the distance threshold in meters.

api_list.name: createWorker
api_list.description: Creating a new worker generates a temporary password which is sent to the worker’s phone by SMS along with download details for the worker iOS and Android mobile apps.

required_parameters.name: phone
required_parameters.description: A valid phone number as per the worker’s organization’s country.

required_parameters.name: teams
required_parameters.description: One or more team IDs of which the worker is a member.

optional_parameters.name: capacity
optional_parameters.description: The maximum number of units this worker can carry, for route optimization purposes.

optional_parameters.name: vehicle
optional_parameters.description: The worker’s vehicle; providing no vehicle details is equivalent to the worker being on foot.

optional_parameters.name: radius
optional_parameters.description: The length in meters of the radius of the spherical area in which to look for workers. Defaults to 1000 if missing. Maximum value is 10000.

api_list.name: insertTasksAtIndex
api_list.description: You may insert one or more tasks at a given index by providing the index as the first element in the array, followed by the task IDs.

required_parameters.name: entityId
required_parameters.description: Id of the container of provided type

required_parameters.name: containerType
required_parameters.description: Type of the container to insert

required_parameters.name: index
required_parameters.description: To append to the end, use -1 as your index. To prepend, use 0. For example, if you want to insert two tasks at position 3 for a given worker, such that all currently assigned tasks at index >= 3 are shifted forward

api_list.name: listAdministrators
api_list.description: Lists administrators

api_list.name: listHubs
api_list.description: A hub is a depot for a team: the location from where all deliveries start for the team's workers, for the purposes of route optimization only; teams can have zero or one hubs. To create hubs, head over to the dashboard.

api_list.name: listTasks
api_list.description: Returns a paginated collection of all tasks in your organization.

required_parameters.name: from
required_parameters.description: The starting time of the range.

optional_parameters.name: lastId
optional_parameters.description: Used to walk the paginated response, if there is one. Tasks created after this ID will be returned.

optional_parameters.name: to
optional_parameters.description: If missing, defaults to the current time. The ending time of the range. Tasks created or completed before this time will be included.

api_list.description: Get all webhooks

api_list.name: listWorkers
api_list.description: List all available workers

optional_parameters.name: teams
optional_parameters.description: An array of the team IDs that workers must be part of.

optional_parameters.name: filter
optional_parameters.description: An array of fields to return, if all are not desired. For example, name, location.

optional_parameters.name: states
optional_parameters.description: An array of worker states, where 0 is off-duty, 1 is idle (on-duty, no active task) and 2 is active (on-duty, active task).
